          "content": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\"drivers/acpi/video_detect.c\"],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\"video_detect_dmi_table\"],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"The Acer TravelMate 5735Z is missing from the video_detect_dmi_table DMI quirks table. The system has ACPI video backlight capability, and the default autodetection logic (in acpi_video_get_backlight_type) returns acpi_backlight_video instead of acpi_backlight_native. However, on this specific hardware, the ACPI video backlight interface does not work properly, while the native Intel backlight (intel_backlight) works correctly. The fix requires adding a DMI entry for this model with the video_detect_force_native callback, similar to the pattern used for other non-Win8 machines that need native backlight (e.g., Lenovo Ideapad models, Dell models at lines 287-354). When acpi_backlight=native is used, the system works correctly because it skips ACPI video registration and allows the native backlight driver to take precedence. The missing DMI entry prevents this from happening by default.\"\n}\n",
