          "sequence": 56,
          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "Perfect! I have completed my fault localization analysis. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Fault Localization Analysis Summary\n\n### Bug Details\n- **Repository**: Linux kernel (torvalds/linux)\n- **Kernel Version**: 5.6.7\n- **Component**: ACPI Video Backlight Control\n- **Device**: Acer TravelMate 5735Z\n- **Issue**: Brightness control via function keys doesn't work by default\n\n### Root Cause Analysis\n\nThe bug is located in **`drivers/acpi/video_detect.c`** in the **`video_detect_dmi_table`** data structure.\n\n**Key Findings**:\n\n1. **Missing DMI Entry**: The Acer TravelMate 5735Z is not present in the `video_detect_dmi_table` (lines 112-377)\n\n2. **Incorrect Default Selection**: The autodetection logic in `acpi_video_get_backlight_type()` (lines 413-450) follows this sequence:\n   - Check kernel command line parameter (not set)\n   - Check DMI quirks table (no match for this model)\n   - Auto-detect based on capabilities:\n     - System has ACPI_VIDEO_BACKLIGHT capability \u2713\n     - Not a Win8 BIOS (2011 laptop) \u2717\n     - Therefore returns `acpi_backlight_video` \u2713\n\n3. **Hardware Mismatch**: \n   - The ACPI video backlight interface doesn't work on this hardware\n   - But the native Intel backlight (intel_backlight) works perfectly\n   - When `acpi_backlight=native` is used, the native backlight takes precedence and works\n\n4. **Evidence**:\n   - DMI data from bug report shows: SYS_VENDOR=\"Acer\", PRODUCT_NAME=\"TravelMate 5735Z\", BOARD_NAME=\"BA51_MV\"\n   - No Acer entries exist anywhere in `video_detect_dmi_table`\n   - Similar models (Lenovo, Dell, etc.) have entries forcing native backlight at lines 286-354\n\n### Why This Is a Bug\n\nThe kernel's video detection logic is working as designed, but the device database is incomplete. The Acer TravelMate 5735Z should be in the \"Non win8 machines which need native backlight nevertheless\" section (line 286) with a `video_detect_force_native` callback.\n\n### Verification\n\nThe result has been written to `/workspace/fault_localization_result.json`",
